wherever I am, dimwit.

95
00:06:45,666 --> 00:06:47,083
It's starting to weird me out.

96
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:49,125
You're not freakin'
stalking me, are you?

97
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:52,458
Maybe I should just off you. Oh?

98
00:06:52,541 --> 00:06:54,083
Hey, sweet score!

99
00:06:54,166 --> 00:06:55,750
Think that's a good idea?

100
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:57,833
Using your deadly skills
to pick up street change?

101
00:06:57,916 --> 00:06:59,291
You're a moron.

102
00:06:59,375 --> 00:07:01,666
Don't you know samurai use
their swords to cut radishes

103
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:03,375
if they don't
have a knife handy?

104
00:07:03,458 --> 00:07:05,708
I saw it on YoTube one time.

105
00:07:09,708 --> 00:07:10,875
[AUDIENCE clapping]

106
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:12,625
[LEO]
So how does your ability

107
00:07:12,708 --> 00:07:14,833
to manipulate your
blood compare to Klaus's?

108
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:16,333
Does it work the same way?

109
00:07:16,416 --> 00:07:18,875
Eh, more or less.

110
00:07:18,958 --> 00:07:20,083
But the effects are different

111
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:21,791
because we don't
use the same style.

112
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:24,750
The chief's got a way with
it that's especially nasty.

113
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:26,041
It's basically like
being attacked

114
00:07:26,125 --> 00:07:27,375
by your worst nightmare.

115
00:07:27,458 --> 00:07:28,458
Yeah?

116
00:07:35,791 --> 00:07:38,291
Ow, man! Watch what
you're doing, dummy.

117
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:40,791
Uh, hey, Zapp.

118
00:07:40,875 --> 00:07:41,833
What?

119
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:42,916
What is that?

120
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,208
Don't mess with me.

121
00:07:44,291 --> 00:07:46,625
It's a dry cleaner's truck.

122
00:07:46,708 --> 00:07:48,625
You don't say.

123
00:07:48,708 --> 00:07:50,750
That's what it looks like?

124
00:07:54,916 --> 00:07:56,666
Wait, are you telling' me--

125
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:58,833
Yes. Exactly.

126
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:00,708
That's no dry cleaner.

127
00:08:06,708 --> 00:08:09,791
What I see is completely
different and way scarier.

128
00:08:11,041 --> 00:08:11,833
[LEO gasps]

129
00:08:14,291 --> 00:08:15,541
The hell?

130
00:08:15,625 --> 00:08:18,208
[LEO] Our eyes met!
We're getting out of here!

131
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:22,333
As far as I can tell, you're
totally neurotic, you weirdo.

132
00:08:22,416 --> 00:08:24,208
So frustrating.

133
00:08:27,250 --> 00:08:28,583
[phone trilling]

134
00:08:28,666 --> 00:08:31,250
[WOMAN] What's up? Getting
ready to die, dickhead?

135
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:33,333
[ZAPP] Not even close,
you evil she-bitch.

136
00:08:33,416 --> 00:08:35,958
There's a two-ton dry cleaner's
truck on Gilda Street.

137
00:08:36,041 --> 00:08:37,208
Track it.

138
00:08:37,291 --> 00:08:41,291
Yeah, Leo says he sees
something alterworld-ly.

139
00:08:41,375 --> 00:08:43,458
Someone's probably
sneaking something around

140
00:08:43,541 --> 00:08:45,291
using high-level illusionry.

141
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:48,291
Nah, it ain't that.

142
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:51,583
I mean, at least, I don't think
the kid's got a mental disorder.

143
00:08:51,666 --> 00:08:55,791
